folder: Trantor Place & Dixon Avenue, Staten Island, NY
text:
(1) Trantor Place, west side, north of Dixon Avenue, showing the J.W. Barnes house. The view is northeastward from Dixon Avenue.

March 24, 1928

P. L. Sperr

(2) Another view of the house, seen from Nicholas Avenue. Trantor Place is the new street being cut through directly in front of the house.

May 21, 1932

P. L. Sperr
